json
  specifies objects as name-value pairs
  validated using json schema
  almost identical to a python dictionary EXCEPT
    in JSON, true and false vs. True and False in python
    JSON uses null, not None

a value can be a string, number/integer, true, false, null, object, or array


required, additionalproperties=false
means you must have what's in the schema and you cannot add anything not defined

select * means select all the columns
